caption: The food was delicious,  atmosphere was very nice. We had the empanadas, buttermilk drops, and biscuits for appetizers. For entrée we had the grits w/ chorizo...all of it was GOOD!! Update to my review....20% Gratuity automatically added to bill so be mindful!!! I was not so cautious and tipped twice 🤨 food and service were great but not happy about the automatic gratuity.
The sandwich I had was great. The water.... tasted like it was from the gutter or atleast from the dish water. Service was friendly.

A rustic-chic, cuban-inspired escape from the norm with a courtyard and bottomless cocktail brunch. It is a refreshing divergence from the expected new Orleans fare and a great place to cleanse the palate of creole spice and fried foods. We had the breakfast sandwich with plantains as the bun. It really made my taste buds consider the possibilities. The empanadas are a must try here. Classic but perfectly executed. The service was on point and so friendly.
Excelente comida, platos muy caribeños y con un muy buen sabor.
Great snacks and wine!
perfect food - try the lamb curry and you won't regret it! amazing people, amazing food, must go in new orleans!
Over priced mediocre food. Not enough wait staff. Wouldn't eat here again.

My husband and I went for brunch and were very happy with their COVID safety measures. There were no tables available outside when we arrived, but they left the doors and windows open and the tables were spaced very far apart so we felt comfortable.  The food was great! We loved the kale salad (sooooo good) and empanadas for starters and the Brussels sprout hash stole the show. He had the burger which was very good - but he kept stealing my Brussels. Both our cocktails were delish - the pina colada and Hurricane. Felt nice to be tourists in our own city for the first time in a long time.

The best most fun meal during our 10 day trip to New Orleans! Chef Nogueira is interpreting Modern Latin American cooking in this hip and atmospheric venue. Staff and bartenders are super friendly, welcoming, and knowledgeable. The cocktail menu is extensive, has something for everyone, and drinks are made with great care and are DELICIOUS! The menu here changes frequently to take advantage of the wonderful seasonal products available in the area. I devoured a whole red snapper, lightly dredged in cornmeal and fried, served in a bold Chile sauce laced with roasted sweet potatoes and served with soft, warm roti. If you're there when Ponchatoula strawberries are available, don't miss them! A beautiful salad featuring them was on the menu when we were there recently, and what a treat to eat locally-grown, ripe, fragrant strawberries I February!  The restaurant did a good job at maintaining social distanced seating and offers outdoor seating in a charming outdoor courtyard. Don't miss this place!
Paella, cocktails , deep fried crackers were all amazing . We love this place, it’s a must visit when in NOLA

Went for dinner, the food delicious and the cocktails were AMAZING! Jonathan is the best and took care of us the entire night, it was my birthday and he made sure it was extra special and gave us so many recommendations! The chef was also able to prepare food dairy free and vegan. Definitely recommend and Jonathan is the best!!!
Love it #porkmafia
Great vibes and yummy, but limited menu. 10/10 recommend the paella

On every vacation get paella for 2. Paella was good but for 35.00 it was a very small amount.   Bread always served but had to ask and was charged extra 3.00.  Also 20% tip added and not told about. Fortunately we caught it and did not tip twice.  We come to no several times a year close to our condo but probably won't go back
Fantastic cocktail menu and food! Very safe and friendly environment during Covid times
Sam is the best!
WOW! First, great staff. Food was AMAZING! Not only was it creative and delicious, it made you feel good. Nutritious and veg friendly :)
Excellent care and service!
Cane and Table hosted a lovely wedding event for some of my best friends! Staff was delightful and food was delicious.
I liked it!
Small, Quaint, and Good. You game a real sense of calm here. The servers were real and friendly.
Omg their drinks are celestial! Good prices. Personnel issweeeet and awesome! Luf dis place. Def recommend for drinks (didn't try food)
Appetizers alone are enough to fill you up, Brussel Sprouts are unreal. Super friendly service and atmosphere. Perfect ratio or Champagne to OJ for mimosas.

Stopped in around an hour before closing time. Told the dude, "We know you close in an hour, but we were just going to get one drink." Tbh he seemed pretty flustered, almost like it was a problem, but I get it. He kinda came around when he grabbed our drink order.  Got a New York Sour and it was great! Didn't get food this time, but this is one of my fav restaurants in NOLA. I def recommend this place! Great ambiance. :)

Watermelon salad! Sounds simple but it is perfection. Everything I've had from them has been delicious and their back patio is like vacationing to a private island. Service during covid is awesome, they have little flags on the table for when you need something to respect social distancing. Can't get enough of Cane and Table!
good and fast service and excellent food items

Fantastic meal, excellent service. Highly recommended. Not pictured is the creole dumplings which were seriously so delicious I forgot to snap a picture. Friendly staff and a cozy atmosphere. We will definitely come back next time we visit NOLA.

I ordered the brisket and the shrimp to go.  The menu items are in Spanish which is different for New Orleans.  Translations underneath.   For some reason the front of the restauraunt was empty, but there were some people in the courtyard area.  The portion sizes seem a little small, but will need to taste the food.  The atmosphere looks nice in the front and the courtyard has a private feel.  I will need to order more.  Seems like a nice quiet spot for a nice meal
Owner and staff were as good as the food. Great experience
Excellent food,  service,  and atmosphere.
Always love stopping in for a drink
Cane and table never disappoints. The is incredible and the staff is charming.
Best Paella I've had! Lemonade was fresh and tasty. Best serves I've had in t he N.O. Definitely going back.

How Cane & Table navigated serving during Covid felt very responsible and well managed for both customers and their employees. There service, when prompted by little markers on the table, was excellent and personable. But what really made the experience lovely was the food and cocktails! We loved every second in C&T’s courtyard. Would recommend for anyone trying to go off the beaten path in the French Quarter. I recommend the Curry, Crab Croquettes and any of their cocktails!!

I had the brisket and rice, which was good, but it was pretty much just plain white rice and shredded BBQ brisket. Nothing special. $21. Perhaps there are other more exciting dishes on the menu I missed.

My husband and I enjoyed our first date night since quarantine here and it was perfect. The courtyard was beautiful, and the food was delicious. The staff was excellent and made it super easy to dine out safely.
Reopening protocol seemed well thought out and flawlessly implemented. I felt very safe and comfortable eating on the patio. And obviously the food was amazing!

Firstly their commitment to safety of their guests and staff is exemplary, it was the first place we ate out at since covid and I couldn't have asked for a better experience or recommend this place enough. Highlights are obviously the cocktails, and the delicious food. The plantains, watermelon salad chicken sandwich and flan were all outstanding. Every drink I cant remember the name of was delicious, and they had topochicos, my favorite bubble water. The service was friendly and attentive, and that patio is adorable and a perfect evening drink spot in the quarter. What a great time!! Compliments to the whole team.
Great food and Staff. Sam is a sweetheart.
Always a great atmosphere in the place - can't wait to stop by again in the near future ❤️ Food & cocktails top notch 👌
Very busy, long wait on week night
Gorgeous location, right in the middle of the action... Expertly crafted cocktails and small plates that will make you forget you are in New Orleans.  Definitely recommend to stop in.

Hard to find but totally worth it! The food and service were exceptional. The staff was very friendly and went above and beyond to help us decide what we would like to order. Highly recommend and we will return the next time we make a trip to New Orleans!
Dimly lit casual restaurant with very high end cocktail and food to match. $$ for the food $$$$ for the specialty cocktails.
Excellent selection of cocktails, ask the bartender for their suggestion you won't be disappointed.
Charming atmosphere, small, great food. Avocado salad was delicious as were the Empanadas.
Great food,  service & ambiance!! Definitely coming back!
Stopped in for a couple happy hour drinks, daiquiri and perfect bamboo. Can't beat happy hour prices!

Loveee this hip, hidden gem on Decatur! the space is really charming/romantic, cocktails are amazing, super-sweet staff.. and the food is gooood, I think I’m addicted to their Caesar salad, best ever..
Hipster heaven
Shared a meal with friends we ordered many dishes from the menu. Everything was tasty and flavourful. Cocktails are great too and the staff is friendly. Beautiful space
Food was good. Service was ok. No hot coffee!
Top notch drinks. Happy hour is a steal. Fried saltines and pimento is surprisingly delicious.
Great place for small plates and drinks with friends. The place is a little hard to find, use the street number versus looking for a sign. The ribs are fantastic.
Great small plates and the drinks are really, really....REALLY good.
Excellent food, service and atmosphere. Outdoor dining is amazing and romantic. Fresh fish and amazing cocktails, need I say more!
AMAZING. Food was delicious. Our bartender Ed crafted us the most perfect & lovingly created cocktails and gave us some great suggestions for other local spots to check out.
Great staff and delicious cocktails.
Food and service were really good but prices are really high. The place is cozy but plan to spend a lot of money there especially if you order cocktail or any alcoholic beverage .
Loved this intimate and tasty place. The people were warm and the food was delicious.  Try everything. It's special, and unlike most places, it was pretty health.
This is my absolute favorite place to go in NOLA!
Been twice now. (Live out of town) this place is excellent they really pay attention to making cocktails which are superb. You really can't go wrong here.
Outstanding food. Varied menu with some pan-hispanic influences. Do not miss the tostones. They are great!

Great space with low lighting, up tempo tunes and arguably the best cocktails in NOLA. Service is stellar, with bar help eager to educate on their craft drinks. Every selection was well balanced with multiple levels.
Oh man.. not my cup of tea. Drinks are too expensive and not very good.

Cool ambiance,  well versed bartenders that are able to offer great recommendations for  cocktail and menu selections.  Stop in, you won't be disappointed! Great space to have a cocktail and share a plate.

Very cozy place.  The food is amazing. I especially liked their rice and shrimp platter that is black. I can't remember the exact name. They are also doing rum flights of all locally made rums for only $25. Totally worth it!

Fabulous food. In a place like New Orleans that offers so many choices, Cane and Table stood on its own merits. The food was amazing and the wait staff were fabulous. They were friendly funny and very helpful. We loved our dinner and will go back before we go home.
Good cocktails. Happy hour 3-5. Very limited food menu till 5.
Great drinks, very good brunch food.

Very expensive and food was horrible. Will not go back. There was 5 of us. $300 dollars later still hungry (starving) after forcing myself to eat what was served. Went to a late night restruant about 2 hours later just 2 of us and spent 30 bucks and satisfied my appetite. Don't know what the fuss was about this place? Was told it was soooo good... What a joke. Chicken was salty (can I please have some chicken with my salt)? The crab balls were good, but how can you mess crab up? Staff was very friendly and helpful though.
Brussel sprouts and shrimp cocktail were delicious.  Had the "open relationship" cocktail which was refreshing!

We just looked up this place and went but our experience was great. The service is fast, food is super tasty.  Their drinks especially cocktail s menu  oh my God, they were so good. Our server was super sweet and got us a desert since we were celebrating. Definitely recommend this place.
Amazing cocktails!

Food was outstanding.  Small plates -we had the most delicious crispy brussel sprouts, black eyed pea fritters, fantastic caesar with Mancero - it was yum, and ribs oh yeah!!! Tres leche and Flan for dessert and a great bottle of Rose.  Service and atmosphere were on point.  You will not be disappointed.

We were really pleased with our experience here. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, the service at the bar was terrific, and we were really pleased by the food. We ordered the yucca, brussel sprouts, and ropa vieja and loved each dish. We couldn't have been happier.

This place is nice, to be fair. Maybe I'm just sick of over priced tiki drinks. I mean, it's fine. Here, you want some tiki? Go get some pineapple juice, whatever rum you like, whatever tropical stuff you got laying around the cupboard. Boom. I just saved you $15. Your welcome.
Delicious drinks, beautiful space
Google has the address but outside didn't see any signs about cane and table
Great food and service.  Not your regular local fare for new Orleans but would go back for more. Thank you
Solid brunch with all-you-can-drink option

The food and the atmosphere here are both amazing. We will absolutely be returning when we come back to New Orleans! We ordered some sort of mushroom and dumpling dish that makes my mouth water to think about 🤤 and the brussel sprouts were just as delicious. Our sever was friendly, attentive and gave us great suggestions!
Excellent food - really well-seasoned. The service was wonderful, and the setting was cozy and charming. I recommend sitting outside.
Get the Brussels sprouts!  This place had a fantastic atmosphere with lovely old back patio, really friendly bartenders and wait staff. Ended up visiting twice for the Brussels sprouts!
Food was so good. Highly recommend going. Outdoor table seats where very nice Also
Five starts for the giant bathroom locks
had the fried chicken sandwich & grits- both great. chicken sandwich had Cole slaw on it, which I like but some may not. grits were grits with butter... great service & good food!

Great food and staff. Great spot for a group. Everyone's dish was delicious. The brussel sprouts were the favorite. The crispy ribs were tender and juicy and crispy all at the same time. Definitely would recommend.

Rude older later at the hostess podium Would not let us order drink at the bar with out a reservation, even though I repeated over and over we wanted a To go drink. This was during southern decadence.  I'm sure because we were in costume that we looked like tourists,  but we are local, and the jig is , walk up to bar, get go cup, pay and gtf out.  That was the plan and we left much sooner than we should have because of the service..
Sneaked in off Decatur St into this intimate setting. Didn't know what to expect.... food, drink, all around vibe in here was awesome. I guess it's always when you least expect it.
Absolutely fantatic food and drinks! We recommend this place to our kayakers all the time!

We LOVE Cane & Table!! Anytime we're in New Orleans, we make sure to visit here. The food and drink are so phenomenal!! We recently had our wedding "reception" at Cane & Table and it was amazing. Justin & team were so helpful throughout the entire planning process and they helped make our wedding so magical. The team is very accommodating, kind, and helpful. If you're looking for a great spot to have a private event or even dinner, make sure to book with Cane & Table!! A huge thank you to Justin & team!!!

Like the food! Ordered Brussels sprouts and chicken - taste great! Rice(?) in chicken is a bit under flavored and chicken is a bit salty though (so I would recommend the Brussel sprouts) a great experience if you don’t want too southern food:)
Thank you Sam for the great cocktails and recommendations. Kudos to the kitchen.
Most excellent cocktails. Tasty food
Absolutely delicious food and amazing drinks. The bartenders put lots of care into what they create and know what they're recommending. Wonderful experience.
Fantastic breakfast and drinks!!!! If you are staying around french quarters and want a good brunch would highly recommend
Delicious

This continues to be one of my favorite places in NOLA. The bartenders are knowledgable and know how to craft a cocktail.  The food gives a nod to Cuban flare simple ingredients yet flavorful.  The atmosphere is a small window in Cuba.  I highly recommend stopping into for a cocktail and see where it takes you.
Fantastic food, excellent service, friendly staff
Their daiquiri is sublime.
Some of the best food we had in New Orleans. The restaurant has a chill island vibe with some outdoor seating (although closed when we were there). The Pina Colada is killer.

Food, drinks, and service once you're seated are always top notch. But we had to sit at the bar even though their dining area was mostly empty when we arrived and never filled up. So, our choice was the bar or the outdoor courtyard on a 100 degree heat index early evening. As much as I like the place, I would have eaten somewhere else rather than sit outside. At no point during our hour there would they have had difficulty seating our party of two. We were well before the traditional Saturday dinner rush.
Service is great, food was very good, and drinks were wonderful! Small little place with lots of ambiance. Truly enjoyed ourselves!
Best cocktails we had all week, and great food too
Very good selection of drink with quality ingredients. The staff were very knowledgeable and friendly. This is a sister bar to the famous Cure. Shout out to Gwendolyn (so?) For the great cocktails!
Incredible brunch. Highly recommended.
Beautiful space, delicious food!

Get the eggs benedict!!! It's unlike any other you've ever eaten. Yummy mimosas. Absolutely delicious, great atmosphere and service. Kind of a hole in the wall. I think we passed it like 3 times before we finally found it haha. It was worth the hunt!
Delicious brunch!
Charming and cool inside, Cane and Table was a lovely escape from the August heat. Refreshing cocktails, tasty small plates - especially crab croquettes - and oh, such delicious flan!

This review is only based on drinks. The bartender was great. We tried four different cocktails. The pina colada, hibiscus, and two that had sherry (one had Icelandic birch liquor). All were great. Would highly recommend going here at least for drinks. Next time I’ll try the food.
My boyfriend and I popped in here on a whim to avoid the heat and crowds of the French Market. We were so IMPRESSED with the food. It way exceeded our expectations! So yummy and filling.
Great place, warm and cozy atmosphere. Perfect for a quiet dinner.
Great cocktails with bartenders willing to offer suggestions.
Best Dinner place we had in NOLA

This place is a gem!!! On Decatur st. if you dont know about it you will miss it!!! No sign to show you where it is, I read about it on pinterest and and made it a mission to come here. By far the best craft cocktails I've had hands down, and I am an avid traveler who loves the craft cocktail style. Amazing Cuban food since I moved from Miami I've been craving a good ropa vieja and I finally found it. Empanadas are to die for spicy flakey goodness. And the staff was friendly and on point. PLEASE Don't pass this place by it's worth the pop in away from the bourbon street madness.
Love their happy hour!
The fried crackers were dope!

This place was amazing! It was recommended to us by a bartender at Cafe Amelie. We stopped in for some apps and drinks and found such an amazing menu! The dishes were creative and delicious. Even the saltines were homemade (and amazing! Saltines!) Highly recommend. Service was excellent, and the location was just fabulous - beautiful outdoor patio!

Lovely drinks, insanely delicious and creative dishes. The patio is intimate welcoming. Staff are friendly and informed. Casual, but not where it really matters. I'd recommend this to anyone who loves food and drink. So glad it was part of our NOLA visit.
It was such a great experience. The food and drinks were amazing and the staff were so nice. I would highly recommend it for any occasion.
Great original dacquiri and snack plate (marinated olives, pork rinds seasoned with curry powder, pickled veggies, marcona almonds, pimiento cheese, deep fried saltines (!!!))

Pleasantly surprised!! The brunch menu was delicious...their fried chicken burger was juicy and cooked to perfection--very rare to find it this good at any restaurant.  Customer service is superb and consistent.   A great place to have breakfast...top notch eatery!
Great drinks, sit and the bar and enjoy a relaxed mixed drink.  Good bartenders.
Delicious food and very nice atmosphere, great welcoming staff.
Sat 35 minutes at the bar on a semi busy night, with 2 bartenders. The only drink we received was a glass of water. We were never approached, very frustrating for such a highly praised bar.
Excellent food and service
WONDERFUL! Excellent cocktails, friendly staff, yummy small bites.  Will be back for dinner next year!
Very good service and hospitable staff. Delicious ceviche shrimps and great selection of rums. Must visit top floors of the building as it transmits special energy.
Classy joint on Decatur with a vibey outdoors

Favorite restaurant of the trip! Hard to find, as the signage is very subtle, but once there, we opted to sit in the courtyard. Everything on the menu sounded great, so we went with 4 small plates. The white gazpacho with grapes was heavenly. Cocktails were tasty and refreshing. Service was friendly and attentive.

This was our last meal of many during a recent week long trip to New Orleans. We had just been celebrating a friend's birthday and decided to eat here since I had never been and they were open on a Sunday evening. We asked to seat in their courtyard area and were able to get a table there right away. I think we were trying to savor our last night in New Orleans because we ordered an appetizer and an entree for each of the four of us. We all decided that the one thing we wouldn't order again were the Tostones (twice cooked plantains) as they were just kinda dry and tasteless. On the other hand everyone loved the Pork Skins with curry seasoning and cane syrup. We also had the asparagus "Elotes" and the Carribean Spiced Ribs appetizers, both of which were very tasty. For entrees we ordered Tuna, Steak, roasted Springer Hill Chicken with Saffron Bomba Rice and Shrimp with Squid Ink Bomba Rice. I really enjoyed the squid ink rice with my shrimp, but we all agreed that the roasted chicken was superb. I wish I could recall the wine our server helped us choose after they were out of our original pick because were were all very happy with it. I just remember it was a lovely, earthy red. Our server, who had been phenomenal already,  capped off a wonderful meal by coming to the table with a slice of Tres Leches cake complete with candle for our birthday friend.  A wonderful ending to a great week in New Orleans.

Their happy hour is one of the best in the area but don't let that stop you from coming in at other times. Their kitchen turns out dynamite food at a fast clip all evening and their bartenders are top-notch. Expect to see a mix of locals, industry types, tourists, pearl-clutchers, freaks, geeks, and everything in between because this place caters to the mouth and the stomach. They get rave reviews from other foodies and there is a good reason for this. You won't be disappointed if you are patient and come hungry.
Very good!
Perfect (hidden) place for great cocktails and Caribbean inspired snacks or dinner.
Friendly bartenders and staff, great cocktails, awesome atmosphere.
Best small plates in NOLA
Wow the French toast is incredible. Great back patio. Fresh squeezed OJ. The rum and bourbon old fashioned was excellent.
Excellent food and drinks! Different and delicious! I recommend!
I WOULD LIKE TO GO THERE!!!!!!!
The whole outing was perfect, from the drinks to food to service! Special thanks to Danni our server who was there when we needed her but never hovering. Perfect.
Sam is an awesome bartender.
Great cocktails, but a little overpriced. Would like to return for dinner sometime since the menu looks intriguing.
Food was delicious. Wait staff knew the drink menu exceptionally well and treated you like family.
(Translated by Google) Best Arros with Chicken in NOLA.  (Original) Best Arros con Pollo in NOLA.
The Drinks and Service was exceptional
Sooooo Good!
What a find! Knowledge bartenders and very unique and tasty cocktails. The flavors are exactly as described.
Awesome and delicious brunch. The menu is limited so if you are a picky eater you may not like it. Bottomless brunch is $45 which is a steal.
Beautiful courtyard and food. The staff was super friendly too
Delicious food and drinks in an intimate and comfortable space.  We shared a bunch of small plates.

Great cocktails with a lot of variety. The "cast away" comes with coconut water ice so add that to your water when your done.  The hummus was decent, I was kind of looking for a meal but they don't serve food until almost the end of happy hour.
Great unique cocktails done right!
Cocktails are good. The kitchen opens at 5pm... There is no lunch and until 5pm it's happy hour and there is no real food only light snacks.
A very hip place with great small plates inspired by Central America and beyond, a cute patio, and tasty tropical drinks with a classy NOLA twist. Definitely recommend!

Stopped here on a whim because there was no wait.  Had the Beef Pepper Pot Stew and it easily was one of the best things I had on this trip.  Beef was exceptionally tender, the stew was spicy and delicious.  Highly recommended!
Amazing cocktails, great service, sexy ambience, and delicious food

Came here for the all you can drink brunch and it was a blast!! We told them it was my bachelorette weekend so they set us up at an awesome table on the back patio and it was perfect. Our waiter was great about keeping the drinks flowing and the group happy! The food is also delicious! Everyone raved about what they ordered. I got the arepa and it was divine.
Great bartender and drinks. Service was great.
Awesome happy hour food and drinks, it ends at 6.  The outdoor seating is really nice, the courtyard is really pretty.

This place gets 5 stars across the board. The food: Modern takes and twists on classic dishes-- really enjoyed the tuna a la planche, asparagus elotes, beef pot stew, and avocado salad.  The service: excellent. Our server knew the whole menu inside and out, from cocktails all the way through to dessert. She was attentive and helpful, and made sure to answer any questions we had about the menu.  The atmosphere: cool, shabby chic kind of vibe that fits right in with the other restaurants in the area. Really liked the layout and decor; we didnt feel cramped even though it was busy when we went.
Great cocktails. Food was pretty good as well but portions are a bit on the smaller end.
Amazing food! Everything was ridiculously delicious. The garlic soup was particularly tasty. Seriously, one of the best meals we have had in New Orleans.

Great cocktail and food was just amazing. We ordered bunch of small plates and couple of large plates. "Small plates" are not small, we shared it between 5 ppl and there were definitely good size. Pork skin was good. Brussel sprouts were seasoned just right. Overall, I would love to go back!!
Definitely recommend the brussel sprouts! Delicious!
Great place for brunch! The food was to die for!

Beautiful, delicious, and great service. It was a quieter spot (compared to the rest of the Freanch Quarter) and was able to easily find a seat at the bar. In ordered daiquiris and a tuna tostada. The tuna tostada had just the right amount of heat and acidity; I ended up ordering another. One of the best tuna dishes I've ever had. Can't wait to come back and try the rest of the menu!
Bottomless mimosa’s you can’t go wrong :) Anazing food

(Translated by Google) If you want to get out of the American fatty cuisine, a culinary gem in Nola. The food was excellent and really nice. Avant-garde wine list with some discoveries. And a very knowledgeable and attentive hostess. Thank you for the lovely evening!  (Original) Wenn man aus der amerikanischen Fettküche aussteigen möchte ein kulinarisches Kleinod in Nola. Das Essen excellent und wirklich fein. Avantgardistische Weinkarte mit einigen Entdeckungen. Und eine sehr kundige und aufmerksame Gastgeberin. Danke für den schönen Abend!
No high chairs??

We had the ribs and potato mash (Had a fancy French name I can't remember). It was so good!!! Fall off the bone, sweet with a little tang. The drink was their winter version of a french 75 called a firefly, I believe. A little pricey of course, but tasty!
I went here for a cocktail and ended up having two. The staff were lovely and knowledgeable. The drinks top notch and the atmosphere delightful. This place is a gem.

Great location.  Brunch is all day--we ate at 3pm.  The drinks at brunch are bottomless with the purchase of an entree.  Biggest disappointed that the black eyed pea hummus was not available at 3.  Would have loved to have tried it.
Gnarly cocktails
Great drinks and food. Always excited to try their cocktails. Highly recommend the brussel sprouts!
If you visit the French quarter you have to come here. Food ,drink,and service is first rate!
Awesome HH, $6 cava and a variety of $6 snack options-  We took the tasty hummus, definitely recommend!
Super delicious food and attentive bartenders
Great Breakfast
Why I loved this place? Best cocktails in NOLA

I ordered one of their signature cocktails and it was way, way too sweet for what I actually wanted. Understand, it was *delicious*, just not hitting what I needed from my booze that night. Bartender (...Matt? I wanna say? Tall, cute, pretty sure it started with an M. Mark? Whatever. Try to find him.) was *on point* with the cocktails he came up with when I asked for something different.  Literally said something drunkenly vague like "bitter, not too sweet, citrusy" and got two or three wonderful drinks I'll probably never get to have again because I didn't ask what they were called.  Anyway, vibe is great. Even packed it was fun. Interesting history to the building, too. It was just a good time, definitely recommend going. Especially if you're into rum. I'm not, but the rum aficionado I was with reckoned they had some great stuff so.
Great atmosphere, perfect drinks, and impeccable service from the bartenders
A nice spot with outdoor seating on a back patio area. Bartenders were thorough. Try their take on a "french 75". We did not actually try the food here. Just lots of drinks. But we will be back.
(Translated by Google) A restaurant grated and very nice. Reasonable prices  (Original) מסעדה רטנה ונחמדה מאד. מחירים סבירים
Dangerously good drinks!
Fun place. Great bar and staff.
Food, staff, and decor are all amazing!
The gumbo and grits were delicious.
Great craft cocktail bar.
The Food was very good, service excellent, and the restaurant filled up very quickly...
Incredible service and next level cocktails.

Came here during happy hour in the early evening, before heading back to the airport. The staff and atmosphere were good and it filled up later on, so probably worth booking if coming for a main meal. I only had some cocktails and some small plates. These were ok, but not as good as other places I'd been to. It is a Jamaican themed bar, so drinks that normally have whiskey/bourbon were replaced with rum. I had an Old Fashioned for $6, but it didn't quite work.
Can’t speak for the entire menu but our meal was delicious. The ambiance was also very nice and the servers were very friendly.
Friendly staff, great crispy ribs!

This is kind of an expensive place. The wait staff may need to pay a little more attention. Food can sometimes be over salted. I recommend going for happy hour. It’s a very nice place with a beautiful atmosphere. The courtyard is beautiful as well. They have nice craft cocktails That take them about an half an hour to make.
Some of the best drinks in town. Order the Scotch and Coconut, tasty !
Spend your fortune here, it's worth it :)
IT'S CANES
Amazing as always...  The Flu cocktail was a hige hit.
True craft cocktail masters without stuffines..

All 5 of us thoroughly enjoyed our food and drinks.  3 of us got the Haitian fried chicken.  Unreal. Service was amazing as well.  And we didn't feel like we paid a lot for the quantity and quality.  Lovely setting too!
This the best craft cocktail spot period and the bathrooms are so amazingly clean.
Loved the cocktails and the map menu was super fantastic for picking drinks!

Superb. It's a little oasis of cool marble and refined cocktails with a casual, welcoming feel. I've been a dozen times and never had anything but the best service and fare. Cannot more highly recommend it.
quality drinks and the seriously the best Brussel Sprouts I've ever had.. but sluggish and ill-informed bartenders are no fun
Amazing! Food was fantastic. Drinks were incredible. Wonderful atmosphere with stellar service.
Delicious food and bites. Go for the fried chicken sandwich. Best I have tried 🤤
Rum Drinks Galore! go for HH and enjoy good prices on a short list of appetizers.
Great brunch and even better cocktails.
Great cocktails, gorgeous bar, service is amazing!  A member of my party was being bit by mosquitoes (outside) and our waitress was kind enough to share some repellent.
Excellent good and service

French Quarter's cozy treasure! Great service, terrific food & fab drinks. Intense drink menu with generous food portions.  Plenty of food!  Will return the next time we are in NOLA.  Highly recommend.
The cauliflower vegetarian dish was the best vegetarian dish I've ever had.

I found this gem through Airbnb as one of the top rated places in the French Quarter. It has a unique environment and you can tell they have a creative staff. We were in the mood for just a light meal so we ordered the Ropa Vieja to share and it was a perfect amount. For drinks we got the Flor de Jamaica and the Luck I've had. The Flor de Jamaica was very ginger heavy but still good. The Luck I've Had resembled an old fashioned in the sense it was smoky, it was definitely a sipper.

Extraordinary taste. I can’t place my finger on what kind of food this is exactly, it’s just darn good. We were able to try the brussel sprouts, gem salad, half chicken, fish, and roasted cauliflower and everything was immaculate. Seriously so good. We also had special cocktails made up that were like whiskey sours with pomegranate. Try them. They’re stellar.

This restaurant is amazing!! The Jamaican Peas and Rice is extremely good. The Black Eye Peas Hummus is extremely good. The ribs are just fall off the bone amazing. And the drinks. The drinks were subtle yet strong. So delicious. Overall the restaurant has a nice vibe. You will not be disappointed 😊!!!
A fantastic, unique dining experience. Head chef Alfredo's culinary skills are top notch. The menu as well as the atmosphere must be experienced. You will leave Cane and Table relaxed and satiated.

Great little bar with solid cocktails and bites. We had the Elite and pork skins to start and both were delicious and perfect drinking snacks. Would recommend for anyone looking for a chill atmosphere or a fancy date night.
Great drinks and food!
The food was great and the staff was awesome.

Food is amazing. Drinks are different in a great way. The hipster service puts a real damper on the whole situation. Whoever is in charge here would really do well to hire people who at least seem like they care a little bit.
Staff was very welcoming and friendly. Nice patio with a great summer cocktail selection.

Cane and Table is a bijou bar on the outer edge of the French Quarter, a block from the French Market and Cafe Dumonde. The menu has some interesting food choices.  We tried the fried pork skins drizzled with cane syrup.  We also experienced a few drinks at happy hour.
Went for happy hour.  Awesome drinks. Cute place.

The food here is legit! Not sure what other people ordered but the roasted brussel sprouts were some of the best I've ever had. Creamy, just the right amount of balsamic and nice and crunchy. The tostones, Jamaican peas and rice and little gem salad were all delicious! Cocktails were tasty too.
Incredible food
Cozy place with really nice drinks

If you go to New Orleans take some time out away from the French Quarter. I am into more crafted style drinks, this place was perfect. Not too far off the beaten path, very quaint and laid back. The bartenders are experts in everything related to spirits.

The place itself is nothing special. The food was ok, but not spectacular. There are places with better food all around the quarter. I chipped my tooth on the seafood, as there were little bits of shell left in there - they should definitely pay more attention to cleaning it in the kitchen. This is especially inportant since the restayrant is extremely poorly lit. Yes, it contributes, I guess, to the atmosphere. But we could not see what we were eating, and the menu was also difficult to read. The cocktails are awesome, though, and the only reason why I give three stars instead of two.
Good drinks

Stopped in for cocktails on a Saturday afternoon on our way to Frenchman street.  I had heard rave reviews about this place and they delivered very yummy fresh made to order cocktails and the service was great too! I had the hurricane which was nothing like the red sugary dyed drink you get elsewhere.  It was made with fresh squeezed juices and hit the spot on a hot humid day!

(Translated by Google) Friendly welcome, the backyard has charm. The surprise was on the plate. Between the salad and the prepared ribs, it looked like a French gourmet! In addition, it is located in one of the busiest streets in the French Quarter. (2016)  (Original) Accueil sympathique, l'arrière cours a du charme. La surprise fût dans l'assiette. Entre la salade et les ribs dressés on se serait cru chez un gastronomique français ! De plus c'est situé dans une des rues les plus animées du quartier français. (2016)
Excellent ambiance. Quaint and comfortable yet chic and delicious. Loved it!!! Absolutely loved it!! The brussel sprouts,  cauliflower,  cracklings, all wonderful, unique and tasty.
Incredible drinks, great service.
Amazing cocktails
Only ordered drinks here and they were AMAZING!!!

Had dinner with a large group of people out back.  It was very nice, but we had some people sitting at the end of the tables and some of the wood is curling up and seemed to be uncomfortable.  I get the ambiance, but I think the tables should be comfortable for everyone to sit at.  We got to sample a lot of their food.  The ribs were absolutely amazing!  I cannot recommend those enough.  The baked trout, on the other hand, I feel was not cooked all the way.  I catch trout and bake them all the time, and this fish wasn't done.  It was mushy and did not flake off as it should have.  Overall though, it was a great spot to have a dinner with 15 or so people.
great drinks.
Lovely patio.  Great food and wine selection.  Knowledgeable server!

This is a cool bar with nice decor...we stopped in for happy hour - it was a good deal. $6 for happy hour drinks and some apps. The drinks and hummus we had were very good...totally worth the money and more affordable than most other places.
Hit or miss on the small plates, drinks good. Really dark inside, to the point it is hard to read the menu.
The absolutely best brussel sprouts I have ever eaten in my life.
Awesome food service!
Amazon cocktails and friendly service
Craft cocktail bar. I had never tried anything like these. I recommend the Flu.

Went here twice. We know one of the bartenders, so we originally went there for drinks.  For our first visit, we sat at the bar. They are not exactly a Tiki-Bar, but they do specialize in Tiki Style drinks. We tried several of them. The ones on the menu have been developed by the people working there. You can also order more traditional drinks as they have a full bar with a broad selection. The servers are attentive, listen to what you want, and will craft a drink based on what you say you like.  On our second visit, we had brunch. There were five of us for this meal and we had a nice seat next to a window overlooking the street. I ordered something called "Enfriolatas", which is made with a Corn Tortilla, Chipotle Black Bean Sauce, and Chopped Egg. Mix it all together, add some Louisiana hot sauce and it was a treat. Others at the table all ordered different things and the verdict was the same.  Service is outstanding; the food was very good; the drinks were great. And, unlike many other bars in the Quarter, the bathrooms are clean. Believe me, that makes a big difference.

Best ribs I've ever had. Meat came off the bone easily with knife and fork. There were six, so its a good portion for a small plate. Also had Brussels sprouts but didn't like them because there was way too much sauce and cheese.
Spectacular mixed drinks, excellent food, and good service. The courtyard patio was lovely on a cool evening.
Fantastic place. Was there for a good friends wedding reception & can't rave enough about the location & the food. Don't hesitate to come here. I definitely won't the next time I'm in town.
Delicious cocktails.  I can't tell you about the food but the cocktails are good.  Able would be proud if he was still alive.
Great cocktails And happy hour too!

The bartenders were absolutely amazing. One riffed a new cocktail for my husband on a whim during a non-peak time. The drinks were spot on, including my flip. The biscuits and gravy with grits and egg were gone in about five minutes after I devoured them. Cannot recommend this place more.
Delicious food, good wine, adorable staff ensembles.
Great cocktails
Decent drinks. Small space with a nice courtyard
Food was excellent!
Below average rum old fashioned.
Enjoyable cocktails, friendly staff
Amazing food and drinks! Staff is fantastic and very knowledgeable.
Dined solo. Sat at the bar. Amazing service. Spectacular ceviche appetizer and ropa vieja with tostones for entree. Would recommend highly. Yum
Fun place with DELICIOUS drinks!
(Translated by Google) Good atmosphere, good food, good cocktails.  (Original) Buen ambiente, buena comida, buenos cócteles.
Very good brunch.  $45 all you can drink for 2 hours, they didn't really time us.  Select food menu. All items were fantastic.
Get the Scotch and Coconut cocktail!

This was definitely the best restaurant we visited. The cocktails were amazing and the  atmosphere was superb. We really loved green rice dish and red snapper wrapped in banana leaf. We would love to come back again.
Had a great dinner here - excellent cocktails, and the patio was particularly pleasant. Great service, too.
Good ambiance and good food but price of pineapple cocktail exaggerated.
Excellent small plates and sides! Friendly, attentive staff.
We came for the Durock ribs but really everything was excellent
Great rum drinks from new to old...
Good selection of rums...including the best white rum ever...Wray & Nephew White Overproof. Ordered the American flyer and it was really good. Friendly service but limited food menu.
Brussel sprouts were divine.

This place is ridiculous! Come! Eat! Drink! Enjoy! Repeat! I need to get here more often! To quote the person that originally recommended this place to me, "The Crispy Ribs will change your life!" He wasn't wrong, and the Crispy Brussel Sprouts aren't far behind at all.

If only we can have more time here. Entrance is kinda hidden, bc there's no hanging sign like rest of the businesses there. Its located between Coop and Trinity. There'sle wording on their door that said Cane n Table, so look out for that. Drinks are amazing, it play with favor very well, complex yet very friendly n drinkable. It was one of the highlights of my trip.
Loved the experience dining here. The food was exceptionally flavorful, the wait staff was next level attentive and the selection of quality  libations was a welcomed surprise.
Had some excellent drinks here on a Saturday afternoon.
Awesome place
The staff is friendly. The mixed drinks are reasonably priced. And the atmosphere is friendly and welcoming. It's low lit with pretty good food.
Great food, great staff!  Fun time!

Cane and Table is a uniquely solid spot in my most preferred French quarter nook. The bartenders are always engaging and professional, pouring some of the best cocktails in town. The plates are also gratifying. Great place for a date or meeting up before a night of wandering and socializing.

These people are so great they have that restaurant up on freret street called cure which is so good. And I really really want to like this place, but as a tour guide I've brought different people there and I've always had a sort of disappointing experience. The last time we were there for example we just wanted to get bread pudding or some kind of dessert and they said they were out of all the desserts they had one piece of flan left. They're missing many things in the menu and the servers seemed almost annoyed that we were coming in asking for it. The time before that there's still many things missing off the menu and I'm wondering why you put a menu out if you can't keep up with it. The atmosphere is great it's an old Creole mansion but they have this staff, this undependable menu, and they try to upsell you on their crazy drinks? Why don't they just try to be a restaurant why don't they try and stick to some old New Orleans Classics because of the venue and because of the location in the middle of all these other places that are going to serve the same drinks even cheaper.

Food poisoning, horrible service, and then burying head in the sand when it comes to admitting they messed up. Soo professional. There a TON of restaurants that actually care and take pride in their food, go there, don't let them ruin your evening
Awesome cocktail program and great food!

Can not say enough about this place! Eclectic menu with inspired creations served nightly....And the bartenders really know their stuff. My wife doesn't like whiskey, and they were able to make something that she wouldn't share with me!  This is DEFINITELY a local gem, one that the tourists probably overlook, which is a shame. Amazing place, oozing with New Orleans charm, definitely will go there next time I'm in town.

Not that good! The jerked yardbird had zero jerk flavor, and the crispy potatoes were not crispy and they were scarce!  Sad, and we were really disappointed. Had to send the cod fritters back as they were not edible. The drink was good but overall, no plans to ever return.
Thoroughly enjoyed the food. Excellent service. Can't wait to return!
Very tasty Latin food with great cocktails
So much fun
Amazing food, amazing cocktails!

DO NOT spend your money here. Service was awful. Waited an hour for food and the place wasn't even busy. Waiter only came to the table twice. Didn't write anything down, my drink was wrong and my expensive steak was wrong (underdone) and ice cold. Much better food all over NO for half the price and I have had better service at a waffle House.

We had an excellent experience at Cane and Table. We ordered all small plates, gumbo, cocktails, and desert. There wasn't a single thing that I didn't enjoy. The service from Molly was also exceptional. I would highly reccomend.
This place is a hidden gem. The rum drinks are absolutely delicious and friendly staff.
